&lt;li&gt;Prepare preliminary layouts, detailed design drawings, and construction documents for civil site design projects using AutoCAD and Civil 3D.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and coordinate site plans, grading and drainage plans, utility plans, erosion control plans, storm and sewer profiles, and related drawing packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design grading and drainage systems that shape land elevations to direct stormwater safely to inlets, detention, or retention facilities and protect sites from flooding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support access and circulation design for roadways, drive aisles, parking lots, sidewalks, and pedestrian connections to promote safe and efficient vehicle and foot traffic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with building orientation and site layout to support project goals such as functionality, visibility, sunlight exposure, and overall site efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map and coordinate utility connections for water, sanitary sewer, storm drainage, gas, and electric service in accordance with project requirements and agency standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help ensure plans comply with zoning regulations, local development codes, permitting requirements, and environmental standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform earthwork analysis, quantity takeoffs, and cut/fill calculations based on existing and proposed topography.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review drawings for accuracy, completeness, constructability, and compliance with company drafting and design standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with engineers, designers, and project managers to maintain design consistency, manage revisions, and meet project schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and maintain project files, drawing revisions, plot files, and related documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
